00:04:14.080 --> 00:04:15.780
What do I see from a marketing strategy?

00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:18.200
Marketing strategy is the analysis of the

00:04:18.200 --> 00:04:20.200
opportunities of the enterprise in the market,

00:04:20.380 --> 00:04:22.080
the choice of a system of goals, the development

00:04:22.080 --> 00:04:23.140
and formulation of plans

00:04:23.140 --> 00:04:24.260
and the implementation of marketing

00:04:24.260 --> 00:04:25.720
activities, aimed at reducing market

00:04:25.720 --> 00:04:27.220
risk, ensuring the long-

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:28.660
term and sustainable development

00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:30.120
of the enterprise.

00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:31.820
But if you comment on this definition,

00:04:31.820 --> 00:04:34.300
we see that without an analysis of the

00:04:34.300 --> 00:04:36.560
capabilities of the enterprise, the company

00:04:36.560 --> 00:04:38.800
will not be able to develop a strategy.

00:04:39.300 --> 00:04:41.500
The company then develops a system

00:04:41.500 --> 00:04:44.360
of goals, develops a system

00:04:44.360 --> 00:04:46.500
of strategies and plans.

00:04:47.540 --> 00:04:49.580
And, of course, the next step

00:04:49.580 --> 00:04:50.980
will be to develop marketing

00:04:50.980 --> 00:04:54.500
measures that will really

00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:55.980
be aimed at reducing

00:04:55.980 --> 00:04:57.960
risk, because if the company

00:04:57.960 --> 00:04:59.960
does not aim to reduce

00:04:59.960 --> 00:05:01.820
market risk, it can

00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:03.040
fail.

00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:05.960
And, of course, one of the main goals

00:05:05.960 --> 00:05:07.960
of any enterprise is to establish

00:05:07.960 --> 00:05:09.100
a long-term, sustainable development

00:05:09.280 --> 00:05:11.860
of the company in the market.

